If you're looking for modern luxury, hit up the Indian Springs.	The mattresses are average, no pillow tops or luxury bedding.	All in all pretty good value for money, but don’t expect the rooms to resemble luxury spa accommodation – they are closer to motel standard.	Ahh as we awoke the next morning realizing we had the luxury to enjoy another ahh filled day.	Right next door is the Oasis mud bath and massage spa, only a few feet from the hotel.	The rooms are updated, but the air conditioning unit is dismal.